      <TextArea editable="false" layoutX="17.0" layoutY="64.0" prefHeight="562.0" prefWidth="501.0" text="Hello! I hope you find my program useful. My name is Tristan and I am currently&#10;studying computer science. I made this program in my spare time for my girlfriend who&#10;loves to cook. I am uploading this for anybody to use free of charge, but donations&#10;are greatly appreciated. If you have any suggestions or questions, email me at&#10;tristanjhume@gmail.com. Thank you!&#10;&#10;Instructions:&#10;&#10;Ingredient field: Enter the name of the ingredient you want to add to the recipe.&#10;&#10;Amount: Choose the amount of the ingredient. If it is not listed, choose &quot;other&quot; and&#10;enter the amount manually when you hit the &quot;Add Ingredient&quot; button. Tip: If you need&#10;to add something like like 1 &amp; 1/8 Tsp but don't know the decimal amount, try adding&#10;1 Tsp and 1/8 Tsp separately to the recipe.&#10;&#10;Units: Choose the units that the ingredient is in. You can choose &quot;other&quot; if you want to&#10;add something such as &quot;packages&quot; or &quot;grams.&quot; These will still be converted with the rest&#10;of your ingredients, but will not automatically change units.&#10;&#10;Once you have entered this information, press the add ingredient option to add it to the&#10;recipe. Repeat for all ingredients that you need to convert before doing conversions.&#10;Click  &quot;Remove Selected&quot; to remove a single ingredient from the recipe, or click&#10;&quot;Clear All Ingredients&quot; to delete the entire recipe.&#10;&#10;Conversions: Click on the conversion you would like to use on your recipe. All&#10;ingredients in the recipe will be converted. Rounding will round to the nearest&#10;easily measurable amount.&#10;&#10;Managing Recipes: Enter the recipe name then click &quot;Save&quot; to  save a recipe to the&#10;Saved Recipes menu, which you can access by pressing the &quot;Saved Recipes Menu&quot;&#10;button. From this screen you can also load and delete saved recipes. Saving a recipe&#10;with the same name as a recipe that already exists will overwrite that recipe.&#10;&#10;This application stores saves in a folder called &quot;Recipe Calculator Save,&quot; which is&#10;automatically created in the same directory as Recipe Calculator.jar. If you want the&#10;folder somewhere else, move the .jar where you want the folder to be and a new one&#10;will be created automatically when you start the application again... or move the folder&#10;with the .jar to preserve your saves. You can then create a shortcut from Recipe&#10;Calculator .jar to run it from your desktop or wherever you prefer." />
